import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x='state', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across different states?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    city_counts = data['city'].value_counts()
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=480, height=480, margin=0).generate_from_frequencies(city_counts)
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.title("What is the most common city associated with a zip code?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    county_state_counts = data.groupby(['state', 'county']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    state_counts = county_state_counts.groupby('state')['county'].count().reset_index(name='county_count')
    state_counts_sorted = state_counts.sort_values('county_count', ascending=False)
    
    sns.barplot(x='state', y='county_count', data=state_counts_sorted, palette='viridis')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of counties across different states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
